  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Description\r\n\r\nIn Status desktop, the text formatting toolbar you can use to format text in messages doesn't show the text quote option. This option can still be used in markup with the `>` markup right before the text.\r\n\r\nThis is related to https://github.com/status-im/status-desktop/issues/6030.\r\n\r\n## Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Write any message on Status desktop, but don't send the message.\r\n2. From your message, select one or more words.\r\n3. The formatting toolbar shows up with the four following options: bold, italics, strikethrough, and code.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nWhen you select the text, the formatting toolbar shows the quote-style text format option and the other formatting options.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nWhen you select the text, the formatting toolbar doesn't show the quote-style format option, only the bold, italics, strikethrough, and code options.\r\n\r\nYou can still add the quote-style format to your text using the `>` markup right before the text.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status desktop version:\r\n- Operating System: macOS 12.5 \"Monterrey.\"\r\n\r\n![Frame 1](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/62282406/184199084-1b89527a-5a75-43ae-aa94-564aea26390f.png)\r\n\r\n",
